My family and I used to eat at Tuscany often since i was young and I remember the food to be piping hot always and the service to on point,  but this last visit wasn't the 5 star treatment I have to been used to in the past from Tuscanys. Reservations can be made online through Opentable. We made them the day of and had no issues. We just left a ceremony for a family member and it was a very important early celebratory dinner for us. We took an Uber to the restaurant even though there is street parking and valet available ($6). Our server was Manuel. Older gentleman with glasses. He seemed nice at first.  But I don't think he was having a good day.  We ordered coffee,  they serve Lavazza coffee.  It wasnt even hot, drank it anyways.  We tried to flag him down for a refill, no luck.  Had to ask one of the other bus boys.  Asked him for more bread, part of the 1st batch was rock hard, Manuel never brought it. Had to ask the bus boy again and we were given better bread. The food came out piping hot and delicious.  3 stars for that. But our server just started handing out the dishes at one side of the table not remembering anyone's order and had us pass them around.  He also never checked on us after we got our food. We finally saw him when he dropped off the bill. We paid with a credit card, signed it etc. Usually,  servers pick it (the black pad that has the signed merchant copy) up AFTER the party leaves, well, our server reached his arm in front of my father to grab it before we even left the restaurant. *Rude. Aside from the great food,  we were extremely disappointed with the service, 2 stars lost for their service. Will we be back? With all the nearby competition. Probably not.
